    <!-- Help Center -->
    <string name="help_center_title">Help Center</string>
    <string name="help_center_content">Welcome to AgriSight Help Center\n\n
Getting Started\n
1) Home Screen\n
 - Use Quick Actions to Capture or Load a crop image.\n
 - See recent results and access core features.\n\n
2) Capture or Load Image\n
 - Tap Capture to take a photo of the crop. Ensure good lighting.\n
 - Tap Load to pick an existing photo from your gallery.\n
 - Frame a single plant area avoiding background clutter.\n\n
3) Analyze Crop Health\n
 - Press Analyze to run on-device ML (offline capable).\n
 - Wait for the result: Healthy, Nutrient Deficiency, Pest Damage, or Disease.\n
 - Review confidence and recommended next steps.\n\n
Understanding Results\n
 - Health Status: The detected condition of the crop.\n
 - Confidence: Model confidence in the prediction.\n
 - Recommendations: Cultural, biological, or chemical tips to address issues.\n
 - Save to Logbook: Store the analysis for offline tracking.\n\n
Working Offline\n
 - All analysis runs locally; no internet required.\n
 - Records are saved in a local SQLite database.\n
 - Export coming soon from Settings - Actions.\n\n
Logbook\n
 - View, track, and manage previous analyses.\n
 - Use it to monitor crop health trends over time.\n\n
Settings\n
 - Language: Switch between English and Tagalog.\n
 - Theme: Choose Light, Dark, or System.\n
 - Actions: Clear all data or export (coming soon).\n
 - Help &amp; Accessibility: Open this guide and adjust text size.\n\n
Accessibility Tips\n
 - Increase text size from Help &amp; Accessibility.\n
 - Prefer high-contrast Dark mode in low-light.\n
 - Use stable framing and hold the device steady when capturing.\n\n
Troubleshooting\n
 - Camera denied: Enable camera permission in system settings.\n
 - Image not loading: Try a smaller image or different photo.\n
 - Low confidence: Capture a clearer image with better lighting.\n\n
Privacy\n
 - Images and records stay on your device unless you export them.\n\n
Need More Help?\n
 - Check updates in the app store for new features and fixes.</string>
    
